title: Best burger ever!
text: Loved the ambience, loved the food. The very best burger I ever had. Will definitely go back. Highly recommended.

title: Nice selection of tasty food
text: Very nice food that is made fresh. The palak chicken and jeta rice is a must try combination and not spicy as well. The masala dosa is also very nice.

title: Amazing restaurant overlooking water!
text: Great service, good choice of food. Fish is fresh and the chef does justice to that! Goes without saying that coupled with outstanding decor and gorgeous views, it's a hidden(or may be just seemed to me, as every table was reserved) gem of Lincolnshire!

title: Nice cathedral and definitely worth a visit!
text: A must see in this nice British city! Well preserved and speaks of a bygone era! I liked the cathedral shop too!

title: Very nice atmosphere! Nice Coffee!
text: Amazing cafe in the middle of city centre! Lots of places to sit and work and chat! I loved the iced coffee range!

title: Amazing! Will go again!
text: One of the most beautiful trails near Ithaca! Great views! The gorge is stunning. I went down with a friend and walked all the way down and caught a bus back to the Uni. Would do it again if ever I have the chance!

title: A must go for anyone visiting Cornell!
text: Went to visit a friend, she took me here! Well worth the price (which is not expensive at all) and lovely flavours!

title: Great views of NYC!
text: Absolutely loved the visit! the surrounding view was incredible! Was very lucky to have a sunny afternoon! The rush was less, also the NYC pass helped!

title: History speaks here!
text: I went for a day trip here, an amazing experience and absolutely worthwhile. Thrilled to have seen the place where "I Have A Dream" was uttered. A must visit!

title: Nice view! Great Walk!
text: I went on a cloudy day for a walk with some friends! Even with overcast weather, the view was amazing! Can only imagine how it will be on a bright day! Will go back again!

title: Lovely and thriving place!
text: Old world charm and very nice shops around! Went around the time of the food festival and the selections were great!

title: Beautiful Minster!
text: Went with some friends and all of us simply loved the architecture and the yard outside. Beautiful on a sunny day!

title: Nice atmosphere and great Tapas!
text: I have been here quite a few times! Like their happy hours, selection of drinks and the tapas! Would love if the tapas are available till a little later than 8.30 though!

title: What an amazing find close to home!
text: Had food twice by now, once eat in and once take away. I simply love their prawn bulgogi! The wild salmon is great too! I will go back at the next available opportunity!

title: Ok food and ok prices!
text: Had dinner with some friends and the selections were nice, the rice can be a little on the dry side but the chicken, lamb and beef dishes that we ordered were nice.

title: Nice visit!
text: Went here as a part of a walking tour, so did not have a lot of time to check around but seemed very well worth having a look at.. Nice architecture!

title: A whisper from the past!
text: Very quiet and an awesome structure of the erstwhile Greyfriars abbey... Tucked away in a back street of the museum...

title: Not sure about the name as I thought it is called Rosie's Cafe Bar and Patisserie!
text: Went here for a quick snack/coffee.. I thought this is a cafe bar and not a Thai cuisine restaurant, but it was a quick visit so I might be wrong! Anyway, the desserts are amazing to look at and as a result had one and that was one of the best Tiramisu cakes I ever had! Great service!

title: Very good!
text: I went here on a local acquaintance's recommendation for brunch! Excellent jacket potatoes! Very nice beverages and good ambience! Service is top-notch!

title: Very beautiful! A must see in Gloucester!
text: Amazing architecture! Free entry and they also let you go to the first floor from where the view inside is grand! Well worth a visit or two!

title: Very nice ambience, excellent food!
text: I went to this restaurant on a trip to Cheltenham.. very good food options, nice ambience. Service is simply amazing! A little expensive but well worth the money! I will definitely go back!

title: Very good in budget!
text: I liked the variety and the quality of food in a good budget. Will go back in other Itsu too. Great ambience!

title: A regular go!
text: Have been here many a times. The food is good in my opinion and not too expensive! The Chicken Pizza is great!

title: Excellent place for a nature break!
text: I wanted some days free of internet and quiet nature time and went ahead and booked the pod in Longnor wood holiday park. One of the best choices of holidays I have made! The campsite is very well organized and nice. We had the best time in the pod. Great for any weather and had all the facilities we needed. Will go back!

title: OK hostel in a great location!
text: At the price, it cannot do a lot better. The location is amazing and it is literally one road away from the British Museum. There are a lot of places to eat around and they provide the breakfast. The washroom can be cleaner. Ok if you are visiting the city for a few days alone.

title: Nice view of the sea!
text: Went to the ride in March on a cloudy day! The ride was smooth and the view even with clouds was great! I can only imagine how nice it would be on a clear day. A little expensive but worth it!

title: Nice visit and recommended!
text: I went alone to the royal pavilions and it was well worth the money. The building and the sculptures inside are beautiful and worth having a look. Definitely recommended for the history buffs!

title: One of the must visit in the world!
text: One feels like they can touch the ancient time in front of the Acropolis! This visit was one of the bests in my life and I will remember it forever. History buffs who are planning, please go soon!

title: One of the cleaner beaches in Chennai!
text: One of the cleanest beaches in Chennai and the restaurants around are amazing! Have been to many a times and will go again!

title: Liked more than Taj!
text: The fact that I liked the ambience of the fort more than Taj says it all I believe! The place is amazing and will be very attractive to history buffs!

title: Achievement!
text: Climbed all the way to the top with a friend of mine! The view is great from the top but definitely not recommended for older people!

title: Overrated!
text: After Buckingham and Edinburgh castle, somewhat a disappointment! Overrated by far. The dungeon experiences were not nice and have an unnecessary gruesome portrayal of history. The actors are very good though.

title: A must visit in Edinburgh!
text: Very nice castle. But there is a lot of walk and steps involved. Even then the experience is amazing and definitely recommended for any history buff, family, and teenagers!

title: A Gothic structure, must see!
text: Very nice ambiance all around! Should be a must stop photo visit for all visiting Edinburgh! You can't really miss it once in Princess street. Very nice!

title: Good food and great price!
text: The food is good with a lot of variety. The price is also amazing for the variation and quality. It can be a little spicy at times depending on taste but I loved it!

title: Very nice ambience and great food!
text: One of the few places around to have molecular cocktails! Great ambience and good food albeit a little expensive. All in all I think it is totally worth going!

title: Amazing ice-cream, cute little place!
text: I loved a small Gelateria in the Syros port area, has quite a good variety and nice ice-creams! Will go back one day!

title: Great gyros!!!
text: I am in love with their food... nice ambience and the food was great as well as the service! Hopefully I will go back some day!

title: Atmosphere is great inside!
text: This does not seem to be a very inviting place at the first glance but the atmosphere inside is very chic-hippy! It could do with a little more variety of food, but the cocktails are great!

title: Very nice local pub!
text: I visited with my friends and this is an amazing local pub to get the greek feeling! The service is amazing and the variety of snacks and food is great!

title: Great Museum!
text: In my opinion one of the most amazing museums I have been. Very tastefully decorated and a must go for history lovers. Also great for family and friends!

title: Very good gyros. A must try!
text: Amazing souvlaki and very near to Acropolis! A must try in the centre of Athens. I loved the variety and the price is so cheap!

title: A dream come true!
text: This was one among my must see list and it was an amazing experience to see it first hand. The entry fee is zero for even UK students and even with the price I would recommend this for a must visit!

title: Rooftop bar/food!
text: I haven't stayed here but a friend took me to the rooftop bar/cafe! The view is AMAZING! Definitely recommended. I assume the hostel is also nice from the little that I saw. The reception was clean and the manager/receptionist was very courteous.

title: Amazing and memorable day!
text: The museum and the collection is super nice and a must see in Delphi. Having a local as a guide also is a plus and I enjoyed the day a lot!

title: A nice treat and good value
text: I was here in mid February this year and with the nice weather, the view was amazing. I liked their deserts more than the rest.

title: One of the beauties to behold!
text: There is a reason this has been one of the 7 wonders of the world and Taj has rightfully earned the place... Everyone is worried about the pollution surrounding but with more awareness this wonder will keep mesmerising thousands of travellers in the days to come!

title: History came alive!
text: Definitely a must visit for any history buff! The place is filled with the untold pain of the people who faced their last moments in desperation...

title: Beautiful gardens with a little sun!
text: I have been here by now twice and I was lucky enough to visit on sunny days. Very nice indeed and will love to go back...

title: I loved the times spent.
text: Compared to British museum and Cardiff Museum, National museum may seem a little smaller but it is filled with a lot of historical artefacts and I loved the time spent here.

title: Steeped in history!
text: Amazing and great castle to visit. The structure is huge and takes the better part of a day to see it all!

title: Flat Holm Island is Amazing!
text: I went with some of my friends to Flat Holm Island! This was a great day out and the memories will be with us forever! The sunset from the island is a view to remember!

title: One of my favourite beaches in India
text: Very nice beach and I have been to many a times. Can be a little more clean and hopefully awareness is spreading towards that!

title: Great visit with my parents!
text: A great place to visit for religious minded people. There are some stairs to climb etc but my parents with mobility issues could do the darshan. It might be a good idea to pay for skipping the line for the elderly.

title: Amazing visit. Definitely recommend!
text: Very well maintained Castell and the walk to the castell is very nice and serene. Definitely a must see around Cardiff!

title: Amazing trip to the Scottish Highlands!
text: The Ness Bus tour was fantastic and Graham was very knowledgeable about the history and culture of Scotland. He was also very enthusiastic and detailed all the interesting things on the way up and back to the Highlands! It was our first time in highlands and it was an experience that we will not forget ever! Thank you Ness Bus and Graham!

title: An amazing insight to the Journey of Titanic
text: We visited as a family to the Titanic Belfast and it was a very good experience for us. Anyone interested in history and fact checking mission will thoroughly like this place! Recommended!

title: Great way to see London!
text: We thoroughly enjoyed the total London experience with the London eye tour with Graham (I might be mistaken in remembering his name!). The tour includes tickets to St Paul's cathedral, Tower of London and London eye including bus and river bus rides as well as the lunch pack! The guide was exceptionally knowledgeable and very courteous to all of us. This tour is a perfect way to see London in a day but can be a little tiresome to elderly people. But the first part is with Bus and they can always rest inside and the guide made sure we had some breaks throughout. All in all very much value for money and great experience!
place: Total London Experience with London Eye, Tower of London, St Paul's

title: A great tour of Giant's Causeway!
text: We visited the Giant's Causeway with the Irish tours including the Carrick-a-rede rope bridge. The coastal Northern Ireland is beautiful and the tour was well planned. Stephan was well versed in the local history and information and we very much enjoyed the commentary. The only thing to keep in mind is the tour picks up people from different hotels so it may be difficult to get good seats for the view, if you are joining from the tour office but I guess for the price this is minor! Moreover, one can always come early for a better seat! Great experience and will definitely recommend.
place: Giant's Causeway Premium Day Tour from Belfast (Includes Admissions)

title: Amazing place...
text: I really liked royal mile. Lots of shops and very pretty road. I liked the fudge shops there too. Definitely recommended.
